                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5045/171: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-08-10T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1925—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 10—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>322. Following from Shanghai: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“August 7, 3 p.m. Referring to the Legation’s telegram July 28, 3 p.m. It
                            has been decided by the naval authorities that the landing forces,
                            except to guard public utilities, will be withdrawn on the 10th instant.
                            After the withdrawal there will remain ashore to guard public utilities
                            120 Italians, 220 British, 125 American marines and 280 Japanese. There
                            will be 980 reserves.</p>
                        <p>It is believed that conditions will justify this reduction though there
                            are more than 100,000 strikers who are potential criminals. There will
                            be no withdrawal of naval vessels in this vicinity.</p>
                        <pb facs="0822" n="696" xml:id="pg_696"/>
                        <p>There is an unconfirmed but persistent rumor that the seamen’s strike
                            will be extended on the 10th to vessels of all nationalities including
                            Chinese. It is not given serious credence and is mentioned only because
                            of the serious consequence if true.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
